text: Keefe Row, at E. 22nd St. and Evans Ave. in Cheyenne, Wyoming, was built in 1892. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1979. It is a row of nine one-and-a-half-story brick residences. All are built on rusticated sandstone foundations. They were designed by Cheyenne architect J.P. Julien.
